[[File:Arashiyama-Bamboo-Grove-Sunset.jpg|thumb|upright=1.25|Bamboo forest in Sagano]]
'''Bamboo Forest''', or '''Arashiyama Bamboo Grove''' or '''Sagano Bamboo Forest''', is a natural forest of [[bamboo]] in [[Arashiyama]], [[Kyoto]], [[Japan]]. The forest consists of several pathways for tourists and visitors. The Ministry of the Environment considers it a part of the [[soundscape]] of Japan.<ref name=cnn-20180406>{{cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/sagano-bamboo-forest/index.html |title=Sagano Bamboo Forest -- a most enchanting grove |last=Cripps |first=Karla |publisher=CNN |date=6 April 2018 |accessdate=29 July 2018}}</ref>

Prior to 2015 there was a charge to access the area.<ref name=straitstimes-20180517>{{cite news |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/bamboo-trees-in-kyotos-iconic-arashiyama-forest-defaced-by-tourists |title=Bamboo trees in Kyoto's iconic Arashiyama forest defaced by tourists |last=Sim |first=Walter |website=The Straits Times |date=17 May 2018 |accessdate=29 July 2018}}</ref>

The forest is not far from [[Tenryū-ji|Tenryū-ji Temple]], which is the location of [[Rinzai School]], and the [[Nonomiya Shrine]].<ref name=cnn-20180406/>

