'''Brandenburg-Briest Solarpark''' is [[photovoltaic power station]], located at a former military [[airfield]] in [[Brandenburg]], Germany. At the time of its completion, it was the largest solar park in Europe.<ref>[http://www.businessgreen.com/bg/news/2122440/-cells-europes-largest-solar-park Europe's largest solar park to open this year]</ref> Equipped with [[Q-Cells]] solar modules, it consists of three sections, namely *Brandenburg-Briest East (30&nbsp;MW) *Brandenburg-Briest West (30&nbsp;MW) *and Briest-Havelsee (31&nbsp;MW) that add up to a total [[installed capacity]] of 91&nbsp;[[megawatt]]s (MW), sufficient to supply the electricity needs of more than 11,500 households.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20140102200342/http://www.q-cells.com/uploads/media/11_11_03_Press_Release_Solar_power_plant.pdf Q-Cells Builds Superlative Photovoltaic Power Plant]</ref><ref>[http://www.q-cells.com/en/power_plants/references.html#12104 Description by manufacturer Q-Cells] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419222026/http://www.q-cells.com/en/power_plants/references.html#12104 |date=April 19, 2012 }}</ref>
