'''Brunsbüttel Nuclear Power Plant''' is a [[nuclear power plant]] in [[Brunsbüttel]] near [[Hamburg]], Germany. It is owned 67% by [[Vattenfall]] and 33% by [[E.ON]]. It started operation in 1976 and has a gross power production of 806 [[megawatt|MW]]. During its lifetime, it produced 130,000 GW hours of electricity, about double the electricity production of Austria. The value of this electricity is about 9.1 billion Euros.<ref>http://www.nuclear-power-plant.net/index.php?lang=en&item=facts</ref>

As part of the [[Nuclear power in Germany#Closures and phase-out|nuclear power phase-out]], it was taken out of service in 2007.<ref name=wnn110211>

