{{Automatic taxobox | image = Fruits of Dracontomelon duperreanum.JPG | image_caption = Fruits of ''Dracontomelon duperreanum'' | display_parents = 2 | taxon = Dracontomelon | authority = [[Carl Ludwig Blume|Blume]], 1850. }}
'''''Dracontomelon'''''<ref>Blume, Carl L. von (1850) In: ''Museum Botanicum Lugduno-Batavum sive stirpium Exoticarum, Novarum vel Minus Cognitarum ex Vivis aut Siccis Brevis Expositio et Descriptio'' (Blume, ed.), '''1 [15]''': 230-231.</ref> (Vietnamese:Chi Sấu) is a genus of flowering plants in the family [[Anacardiaceae]].
The most commonly eaten species is ''[[Dracontomelon duperreanum]]'', which produces an edible fruit that is eaten in [[Cambodia]], [[Vietnam]] and [[China]]. In [[Vietnamese language|Vietnamese]], the plant is called ''[[:vi:Cây sấu|cây sấu]]'' and is a common urban tree in [[Hanoi]]; the fruit is called ''quả sấu''. The fruit is used in [[Vietnamese cuisine]] both as a [[souring|souring agent]] and a candied treat similar to the Japanese [[umeboshi]]. The treat is popular among youths. In Chinese, the fruit is called 仁面.
==Species== [[File:Nakatambol tree, Dracontomelon vitiense, Vatthe Conservation Park, Espiritu Santo, Vanuatu. An underutilised tropical fruit tree..jpg|thumb|300px|''Dracontomelon vitiense'' − [[Espiritu Santo]] island, [[Vanuatu]].]] *''[[Dracontomelon costatum]]'' Blume - Borneo, Sumatra *''[[Dracontomelon dao]]'' Merr. & Rolfe (many synonyms) - SE Asia to Solomon Islands *''[[Dracontomelon duperreanum]]'' Pierre (syn. ''D. sinense'') - southern China & Vietnam *''[[Dracontomelon lenticulatum]]'' Wilkinson<ref>[http://www.theplantlist.org/tpl1.1/record/kew-2777584 The Plant list (20 January 2018)]</ref> - New Guinea *''[[Dracontomelon macrocarpum]]'' Li - China (Yunnan) *''[[Dracontomelon petelotii]]'' Tardieu - northern Vietnam<ref>[https://www.gbif.org/species/3660211 GBIF: ''Dracontomelon petelotii'']</ref> *''[[Dracontomelon schmidii]]'' Tardieu - Vietnam *''[[Dracontomelon vitiense]]'' [[Heinrich Gustav Adolf Engler|Engl.]] - Vanuatu, Fiji, Tonga, Western Samoa (Upolu)
The following are known synonyms: *''[[Dracontomelon cuspidatum]]'' Blume: syn. of ''[[Dacryodes rostrata]]'' (Bl.) H. J. Lam *''D. laoticum'' Evrard & Tardieu: syn. of ''[[Protium serratum]]'' (Wall. ex Colebr.) Engl. *''D. pilosum'' [[Berthold Carl Seemann|Seem.]]: syn. of ''[[Dysoxylum mollissimum]]'' subsp. molle (Miq.) Mabb. *''D. papuanum'' Lauterb.: syn. of ''[[Protium (plant)|Protium]] macgregorii'' (F.M.Bailey) Leenh. *''D. multijugum'' Radlk. (formerly [[Anne Casimir Pyrame de Candolle|C.DC.]]): syn. of ''[[Toona ciliata]]'' var. multijuga (Kurz) Panigrahi & S.C.Mishra
