{{unreferenced|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox power station | name = Fyn Power Station | image = Fynsværket.jpg | image_caption = Fyn Power Station | location_map = Denmark | location_map_caption= Location of Fyn Power Station in Denmark | country = [[Denmark]] | location = [[Odense]] | coordinates = {{coord|55|25|47.3|N|10|24|39.6|E|region:DK_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | owner = [[Vattenfall]] | status = Operational | th_fuel_primary = [[Coal]] | th_fuel_secondary = Municipal waste | th_fuel_tertiary = Biomass (straw) | th_combined_cycle = | ps_electrical_capacity= 656&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]] | commissioned = 1953 | decommissioned = }}
The '''Fyn Power Station''' ({{lang-da|Fynsværket}}) is a coal, straw and municipal waste-fired power station operated by [[Vattenfall]] in [[Odense]], [[Denmark]]. It has eight units, three of which were operating {{As of|2010|lc=on}}: unit 3, unit 7, and unit 8. Unit 3 has a power of 235&nbsp;MW (coal), unit 7 of 362&nbsp;MW (coal), unit 8 of 35&nbsp;MW biomass), and Odense CHP plant 24&nbsp;MW. Unit 7 has a {{convert|235|m}} tall chimney, which is the second-tallest in Denmark, unit 3 a {{convert|141|m}} tall chimney.
