'''Ingeborg Gjærum''' (born 16 April 1985) is a Norwegian [[environmentalism|environmentalist]].

She hails from [[Ottestad]].<ref name=ottestad>{{cite news|title=Naturlig stor i kjeften|last=Harstad|first=Lisbet|date=18 January 2008|work=Nationen|language=Norwegian}}</ref> She broke national news in 2005, when she was a central board member of [[Natur og Ungdom]].<ref>{{cite news|title=20 millioner til deponering av CO2|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=10 November 2005|language=Norwegian}}</ref> She was deputy leader from 2006 to 2008, and became leader in 2008.<ref name=ottestad/> She remained so until 2009.

In 2010 she was hired by the public relations firm [[Burson-Marsteller]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Kaprer rådgivere fra miljøbevegelsen|last=Hovland|first=Kjetil M.|date=28 April 2011|work=Teknisk Ukeblad|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

